SUMMARY:Voltage Control's FREE Facilitation Lab RDU
DESCRIPTION:Facilitation isn’t mastered by reading about it — it’s built through practice. Facilitation Lab RDU is an interactive session designed to help you sharpen your skills in real time\, alongside others who care about meaningful collaboration. \nThis lab centers on the Practice Playground format\, where participants actively engage in facilitating\, role-playing\, observing\, and offering feedback. Instead of discussing theory\, you’ll work directly with real challenges in a supportive and structured environment. \nBring something you’re currently navigating — a workshop you’re refining\, a team that feels stuck\, or a moment you want to handle differently next time. Through guided exercises and peer input\, you’ll experiment with approaches\, gain new perspectives\, and build confidence in your facilitation choices. \nJoin a community of practitioners committed to creating stronger conversations\, better collaboration\, and more impactful group experiences.
URL:https://downtowndurham.com/event/voltage-controls-free-facilitation-lab-rdu/
LOCATION:BaySix: Space for Good\, 414 Dupont Cir\, Raleigh\, 27603
CATEGORIES:Business Event,Classes & Workshops
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://downtowndurham.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/3.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Voltage Control":MAILTO:info@voltagecontrol.com
GEO:35.7754451;-78.6485734
